First Normal Form (1NF)

Requirements:

No repeating groups.
Each field contains only one value (atomic values).
Each row has a unique primary key.

Example:

Employee
| EmployeeID | EmployeeName | Email                                     |
| ---------- | ------------ | ----------------------------------------- |
| 1          | James        | [james@email.com](mailto:james@email.com) |





Second Normal Form (2NF)

Requirements:

Already in 1NF.
All non-key attributes depend on the whole primary key.

Example:

Instead of storing department details in the Employee table:

Bad

| EmployeeID | EmployeeName | DepartmentName |

Separate into:

Department

| DepartmentID | DepartmentName |

Employee

| EmployeeID | EmployeeName | DepartmentID |









Third Normal Form (3NF)

Requirements:

Already in 2NF.
No transitive dependencies.
Non-key attributes depend only on the primary key.

Instead of:

Employee

| EmployeeID | EmployeeName | DepartmentLocation |

Move the location to the Department table.

Department

| DepartmentID | DepartmentName | Location |

Employee

| EmployeeID | EmployeeName | DepartmentID |
